# ── OS junk ─────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# ── Editor / tooling junk ───────────────────────────────
*.bak
*.tmp
*~
.vscode/

# ── Arduino / embedded build artifacts ──────────────────
*.hex
*.elf
build/

# ── Large binaries (keep the repo lightweight) ──────────
# CAD and archives are ignored by default so the repo stays small and
# clones stay fast. Export a lightweight PNG/PDF screenshot of your CAD
# into 05_media/photos/ instead — that is what shows in the portfolio.
*.zip
*.STEP
*.stp
*.stl
#
# ── Need to version real CAD later? Two options ─────────
# 1. Un-ignore ONE file type by adding a negation line BELOW the rules
#    above, e.g. to start tracking STL files, add:
#        !*.stl
#    (a line starting with ! re-includes a pattern that was ignored)
#    You can also un-ignore a single file:  !05_media/gripper.stl
#
# 2. For CAD-heavy projects, use Git LFS (Large File Storage) so big
#    binaries do not bloat the repo:
#        git lfs install
#        git lfs track "*.stl"
#        git add .gitattributes
#    Then remove the matching ignore line above so LFS can track them.
